The two things the Foundation wants to locate are PoI-7643 and the WWS team. Restructuring this sentence would make this point clear, and the writing more concise. Saying the location of the origin is redundant – 'origin' is defined as a place, so this is like saying  That the origin might be another universe is inherent. Here's how I'd rewrite it:



The location and origin  of PoI-7643 () and  the WWS research team responsible for initial categorisation and their universe(s) of origin are currently unknown.
附加记录：    




Although the event on 29/07/2015 is both funny and interesting, I'm perplexed by how the nature and timing of William Henry Harrison's death was brought up in a  among Foundation personnel. It's not completely implausible – knowing my friends and colleagues, this might conceivably come up. But here, it seems to show up solely for convenience' sake.

I like this as a simple and original idea – a big -pede that burrows through other universes, hard to contain and understand. What makes this is how these complications seemingly pit the Foundation against the Wilson's Wildlife Solutions, whose dynamic piqued my interest when I first learned of them; but then there's the twist that they've been communicating with staff from an alternate universe. Your piece induced me to look up the Boring Agreement before continuing to read, and left me wanting to learn more about WWS.

Overall, I think this is cool. Not compelling, not evocative, not thought-provoking; just cool. I may be missing some aspect of this millipede – the title and other puzzling details hint at something more. But right now, this just reads as an interesting SCP.







